{
  "texts": [
    "**Social desirability bias**: I may present myself in a more favorable light, even if it doesn't accurately reflect my cognitive processes. 3.",
    "**Lack of self-awareness**: I may not have a complete understanding of my own cognitive processes, leading to incomplete or inaccurate explanations.",
    "**Verifying Cognitive Processes** To mitigate these limitations, I rely on various methods to verify my cognitive processes: 1.",
    "**Behavioral observations**: I observe my own behavior, such as my decision-making processes, reaction times, and error rates, to gain insight into my cognitive functioning. 2.",
    "**Neurophysiological measures**: I use neurophysiological measures, such as functional magnetic resonance imaging (fMRI), electroencephalography (EEG), or magnetoencephalography (MEG), to study my brain activity and neural processes.3."
  ]
}